HEADWORD: Superaltar
<hw>Su"per*al`tar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>
<def>A raised shelf or stand on the back of an altar, on which different
objects can be placed; a predella or gradino.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Superangelic</ent>⟦br⟧
